    "nypl_url": "https://digitalcollections.nypl.org/items/b05480a0-c54d-012f-9d66-58d385a7bc34",
    "original_title": "Manhattan: 178th Street (West) - Cedar Avenue",
    "text": "Fort Washington Park: Southward from the pedestrian bridge crossing the New York Central Railroad tracks, at a point about on a line with West 178th Street, The area to the right forms what was formerly known as Jeffrey's Hook, a promontory upon which a light house sets. It boasted, at one time, a one gun \"lumette\" or moon shaped battery built in 1775, overlooking the spot where ships were sunk in an effort to obstruct the British fleet during the American Revolution.\nView 2, of this set is similar though several years later.\n\n1923.\nView 2: May 27, 1927.\n\nP. L. Sperr.\n",
    "text_source": "gpt",
